BindingDB_Patents: Receptor Assay. Competitive binding test for receptors: 20 microl of each of the test compounds and 20 microl of the radioactive ligand together with 160 microl of the receptor proteins were added into the reaction tubes, and the final concentrations of the test compound and the positive drug were all 10 micromol/L. After 50 min of incubation in 30 degrees  C. water bath, the tubes were immediately moved to ice bath to terminate the reactions. GF/C glass fiber filter papers were used for rapid sucking filtration on a Millipore cell sample collector, elution buffer (50 mM Tris-HCl, PH 7.4) was applied for 3 mlx3 times, and microwave was applied for 4-5 min for drying. The filter papers were moved into 0.5 ml centrifuge tubes, and 500 microl of lipid-soluble scintillation solution was added. The tubes were allowed to stand still for over 30 min in dark, and the intensities of radioactivity were measured by a counter.
